 108:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  * @param [out] stat1      Pointer to a variable for holding stat1. Can be NULL.
 109:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  * @param [out] stat2      Pointer to a variable for holding stat2. Can be NULL.
 110:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  * @param [out] irq_status Pointer to a variable for holding irq_status. Can be NULL.
 111:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  *
 112:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  * @returns Operation status
 113:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  *
 114:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  * @remark To simplify system integration, this function does not actually execute the GetStatus co
 115:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  * require bidirectional SPI communication. It obtains the stat1, stat2, and irq_status values by p
 116:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  * SPI read (which is required to send null/NOP bytes on the MOSI line). This is possible since the
 117:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  * values automatically whenever a read that does not directly follow a response-carrying command i
 118:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  * Unlike with the GetStatus command, however, the reset status information is NOT cleared by this 
 119:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  * @ref lr11xx_system_clear_reset_status_info may be used for this purpose when necessary.
 120:../../../lr11xx/lr11xx_driver/src/lr11xx_system.h ****  */
